Friends decompress on the quad, comparing which companies responded warmly, marking target employers on the event map as the aroma of coffee and catered snacks spreads from the lounge. Human resources teams jot notes on tablets while students introduce themselves during the event, some rehearsing elevator pitches quietly against the wall. Students clutch resumes inside branded folders, and as the day winds down, interview sign-up sheets fill with names. Recruiters remind students to follow up with personalized emails.
